description: A dashboard for visualizing results from the k6.io load testing tool, using the InfluxDB exporter

targets.query: SELECT * FROM my_trend ORDER BY time DESC LIMIT 50;
SELECT count("value") as Total FROM "http_req_receiving" WHERE $timeFilter GROUP BY "name", "status", "method"
SELECT count("value") as status FROM "http_req_receiving" GROUP BY "status"
SELECT count("value") as "Total Requests" FROM "http_reqs" GROUP BY "value"
SELECT sum("value") as "Total Requests Errors" FROM "errors" GROUP BY "value"
SELECT count("value") as "Total Requests" FROM "http_reqs" GROUP BY "value"
SELECT sum("value") as "Total Requests Errors" FROM "errors" GROUP BY "value"
SELECT count("value") as method FROM "http_req_receiving" WHERE $timeFilter GROUP BY "method"
SELECT count("value") as "Total Requests" FROM "http_req_receiving" GROUP BY "value"
SELECT count("value") as "Total Requests Success" FROM "checks" WHERE value > 0 GROUP BY "value"
SELECT sum("value") as "Total Requests Errors" FROM "errors" GROUP BY "value"
SELECT count("value") FROM "errors" WHERE "value" = 1 AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time($__interval) fill(none)
SELECT mean("value") FROM $Measurement WHERE $timeFilter
SELECT max("value") FROM $Measurement WHERE $timeFilter
SELECT median("value") FROM $Measurement WHERE $timeFilter
SELECT min("value") FROM $Measurement WHERE $timeFilter and value > 0
SELECT percentile("value", 90) FROM $Measurement WHERE $timeFilter
SELECT percentile("value", 95) FROM $Measurement WHERE $timeFilter
SELECT max("value") FROM /^$Measurement$/ WHERE $timeFilter and value > 0 GROUP BY time($__interval) fill(none)
SELECT percentile("value", 95) FROM /^$Measurement$/ WHERE $timeFilter and value > 0 GROUP BY time($__interval) fill(none)
SELECT percentile("value", 90) FROM /^$Measurement$/ WHERE $timeFilter and value > 0 GROUP BY time($__interval) fill(none)
SELECT min("value") FROM /^$Measurement$/ WHERE $timeFilter and value > 0 GROUP BY time($__interval) fill(none)
SELECT "value" FROM $Measurement WHERE $timeFilter and value > 0
